        "whatBannerText": "What exactly is web programming?",
        "whatBannerDesc": "Find out what web programming is all about!",
        "what": [
            {
                "id": "core-languages",
                "image": "https://wavemakerfutureproof.github.io/content_data/codingAndProgramming/images/web/web-programming/what-1.svg",
                "text": "Programming a website is one of the most popular methods of developing a website in the world."
            },
            {
                "id": "core-capalities",
                "image": "https://wavemakerfutureproof.github.io/content_data/codingAndProgramming/images/web/web-programming/what-2.svg",
                "text": "This is largely because alternative, easier methods such as CMS and web builders are relatively new and therefore not as commonly practiced at this time."
            },
            {
                "id": "Third-Image",
                "image": "https://wavemakerfutureproof.github.io/content_data/codingAndProgramming/images/web/web-programming/what-3.svg",
                "text": "Other than that, programming is a method that is completely free to learn and is something that is taught as a fundamental skill to practice for both introductions to web and programming in general."
            },
            {
                "id": "code-home-appliances",
                "image": "https://wavemakerfutureproof.github.io/content_data/codingAndProgramming/images/web/web-programming/what-4.svg",
                "text": "When broken down, web programming can be defined by 3 core languages. These are HTML, JavaScript and CSS."
            },
            {
                "id": "code-automotive",
                "image": "https://wavemakerfutureproof.github.io/content_data/codingAndProgramming/images/web/web-programming/what-5.svg",
                "text": "These 3 are the staple of any web application and are featured in almost all web applications in some form or other."
            },
            {
                "id": "code-tv",
                "image": "https://wavemakerfutureproof.github.io/content_data/codingAndProgramming/images/web/web-programming/what-6.svg",
                "text": "When combined together, they create the backbone for any website or application. Providing a web structure, design features and basic functionality."
            },
            {
                "id": "code-tweet",
                "image": "https://wavemakerfutureproof.github.io/content_data/codingAndProgramming/images/web/web-programming/what-7.svg",
                "text": "It is important to understand how all 3 of these languages work , because they work together."
            },
            {
                "id": "code-console",
                "image": "https://wavemakerfutureproof.github.io/content_data/codingAndProgramming/images/web/web-programming/what-8.svg",
                "text": "For example, you couldn’t create a webpage using just JavaScript & CSS with no HTML. Just like you couldn’t create a pretty webpage with just HTML & JavaScript. Or a functional webpage with just HTML & CSS."
            },
            {
                "id": "code-microwave",
                "image": "https://wavemakerfutureproof.github.io/content_data/codingAndProgramming/images/web/web-programming/what-9.svg",
                "text": "All 3 technologies are needed to get the maximum potential out of a web page in its most simple form."
            }
        ],
        "whyBannerText": "Why do we code?",
        "whyBannerDesc": "Find out why us humans are so fond of programming and coding!",
        "why": [
            {
                "id": "code-precice",
                "image": "/images/intro-to-coding/introduction-to-coding//images/intro-to-coding/introduction-to-coding/robotics2.svg",
                "text": "Code is a precise set of instructions explaining exactly what you want the computer to do at any given moment. "
            },
            {
                "id": "code-react",
                "image": "/images/intro-to-coding/introduction-to-coding/robotics2.svg",
                "text": "Computers need to know exactly how to react to things, whether clicking a button or tapping the screen."
            },
            {
                "id": "code-direction",
                "image": "/images/intro-to-coding/introduction-to-coding/robotics2.svg",
                "text": "It’s like giving directions to someone on how to get somewhere."
            },
            {
                "id": "code-consider",
                "image": "/images/intro-to-coding/introduction-to-coding/robotics2.svg",
                "text": "You don’t only need to give the directions, you also have to give solutions for other elements that need to be considered."
            },
            {
                "id": "code-example",
                "image": "/images/intro-to-coding/introduction-to-coding/robotics2.svg",
                "text": "For example, what if there is a traffic jam? Or what if your car breaks down?"
            },
            {
                "id": "code-circumstance",
                "image": "/images/intro-to-coding/introduction-to-coding/robotics2.svg",
                "text": "You need to tell the computer what to do in these circumstances and how to behave."
            }

        ],
